1. Theoretical models                                             4925 1451
 The POD code is based on the spherical optical model, the        4925 1451
distorted-wave Born approximaiton (DWBA), one-component exciton   4925 1451
preequilibrium model, and the Hauser-Feshbach-Moldauer statis-    4925 1451
tical model.  With the preequilibrium model, semi-empirical       4925 1451
pickup and knockout process can be taken into account for         4925 1451
composite-particle emission.  The gamma-ray emission from the     4925 1451
compound nucleus can be calculated within the framework of the    4925 1451
exciton model.  The code is capable of reading in particle        4925 1451
transmission coefficients calculated by separate spherical or     4925 1451
coupled-channel optical model code. In this evaluation, the OPTMAN4925 1451
code /7/ was employed for neutrons, while the ECIS code           4925 1451
/9/ was adopted for charged particles.                            4925 1451
